===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}}: an overhead view of a construction, likely a {{lang|zh|亞}}-shaped tomb. Perhaps borrowed phonetically to mean "second; inferior".

===Etymology 1===
Probably from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*ʔrak||inferior; dependent}}, whence {{cog|bo|རག||to depend on; subject; subservient; dependent}} ({{zh-ref|Bodman, 1980}}; {{zh-ref|Coblin, 1986}}).

{{zh-ref|Karlgren (1957)}} connects it to {{och-l|惡|evil|id=3}}, but {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} considers this to be unlikely due to the semantics.

The ''shangsheng'' pronunciation in Mandarin (''yǎ'') is a result of influence from the pronunciation of {{zh-l|啞}}, whose written form contains {{lang|zh|亞}} as a component ({{zh-ref|Fu, 1958}}).

